addPoolLiquidity(address,address,address.details: This function is compliant with any created project ERC20 token and also with ETH values Caller can either provide simple amounts as parameter or give some Ethers as value. Tokens addresses could have been enought to determine pool address thanks to Clones factory, but giving pool address here is gas saving.

params._amountX: The amount of first token. MUST be 0 _tokenX is WETH address
params._amountY: The amount of the second token. MUST be 0 _tokenY is WETH address

params._totalSupply: The total supply of tokens that would be created if the project ICO reaches its goal

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._amountLP: The amount of LP token to give back to the pool.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setFactories(address,address).details: This function is reserved for deployer, and needs to be called to initialize factories addresses

params._amountOut: The amount of other token provided by the pool that caller want to get. Providing the output amount allows the protocol to determine required input amount in the limit of available liquidities Caller needs to compute output amount before calling this function. For this purpose, Pool contract provides `computeMaxOutputAmount` function
params._tokenIn: The address of token caller owns and want to exchange.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

abortProject(uint256).notice: Allows Fans Society to abort a project

addPoolLiquidity(address,address,address.notice: Allow anyone to add liquidity on specified pool

claimProjectTokens(uint256).notice: Can be called by ICO participant when project has been validated by partner (status launched) This will reward the participant with the created ERC20 token

commitOnProject(uint256).notice: Allows anyone to participant to the project ICO ETH value is expected here, and should match with project ICO settings (min, max...)

createProject((string,string,string,stri.notice: Allows Fans Society deployer to create a new project

getEthUsdPrice().notice: Allow to retrieve ETH / USD price with Chainlink aggregator

launchProject(uint256).notice: This function can be called only by project owner (partner) when a project reached is target (status compeleted)

removePoolLiquidity(address,uint256).notice: Allow liquidity providers to remove liquidity on specified pool Caller MUST own LP tokens to be able to use this function. LP tokens will be burnt, and ERC20 and/or ETH will be returned to the caller

swap(address,address,uint256).notice: Allow anyone to exchange ERC20 tokens (ETH is supported)

withdrawOnProject(uint256).notice: Allows any participant of a project ICO to withdraw his funds
